00:00:50.780 --> 00:00:54.140
Some other reasons to
learn the command line is

28
00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:57.260
because it is the only thing
that every Linux system has.

29
00:00:57.260 --> 00:00:58.970
It's the only common thing

30
00:00:58.970 --> 00:01:00.965
that you'll find across
all Linux systems.

31
00:01:00.965 --> 00:01:03.715
Desktop distributions are going
to be slightly different.

32
00:01:03.715 --> 00:01:06.470
Sometimes in recovery
scenarios, for instance,

33
00:01:06.470 --> 00:01:09.890
you might not even have access
