00:03:05.345 --> 00:03:06.860
there's a command called PWD,

76
00:03:06.860 --> 00:03:08.915
which stands for Print
Working Directory.

77
00:03:08.915 --> 00:03:10.355
This will tell me where I'm at

78
00:03:10.355 --> 00:03:12.235
in the directory hierarchy.

79
00:03:12.235 --> 00:03:13.950
If I'm at a random command line,

80
00:03:13.950 --> 00:03:15.030
I type PWD,

81
00:03:15.030 --> 00:03:16.110
I can see that I'm actually

82
00:03:16.110 --> 00:03:20.055
at home/ecen 5013
in the file system.

